Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional). Pop onto a large
lined #baking tray{}.

Toss with half the @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste},
@pepper{to taste}, and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn
the tray halfway through.

Meanwhile, lay the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%g} on a separate lined baking tray.

Toss with remaining @Thai Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste},
@pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal
> due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

When the chicken has been in the oven for 15 mins, toss the
@broccolini{150%g} with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} and season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pop onto the tray alongside the chicken.

Spread the @Teriyaki Sauce{1%sachet} over the chicken.

Return to the oven for the remaining time, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Once cooked, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm thick slices, then divide
between plates.

Spoon over any excess teriyaki sauce from the tray.

Serve with potatoes and roasted broccolini alongside.

Finish with a dollop of @mayo{2%sachets}.